LLM Governance Dashboard
Version: 1.0.0
Build Date: 2025-11-16
Git Commit: 9b307987f0e7de7ce5c46f31a92ff8cd5b58cc00
Release Type: Stable
Release Name: "Foundation"

CHANGELOG SUMMARY (v1.0.0):

FEATURES:
- Complete microservices architecture (8 services)
- Authentication with JWT, OAuth2, and MFA
- Role-based access control (RBAC) with inheritance
- Policy engine with 6 policy types
- Immutable audit logging with integrity verification
- Real-time metrics collection with TimescaleDB
- Cost tracking and forecasting
- Multi-provider LLM integration (OpenAI, Anthropic)
- SvelteKit dashboard with real-time updates
- Docker and Kubernetes deployment support
- Comprehensive test suite (300+ tests)
- Complete documentation

SERVICES:
- API Gateway (Port 8080)
- Auth Service (Port 8081)
- User Service (Port 8082)
- Policy Service (Port 8083)
- Audit Service (Port 8084)
- Metrics Service (Port 8085)
- Cost Service (Port 8086)
- Integration Service (Port 8087)
- Frontend (Port 3000)

TECHNICAL STACK:
Backend: Rust 1.75+ with Actix-web
Frontend: SvelteKit with TypeScript
Database: PostgreSQL 14+ with TimescaleDB
Cache: Redis 7+
Deployment: Docker, Kubernetes, Helm

REQUIREMENTS:
- CPU: 4+ cores (8+ recommended)
- RAM: 8 GB minimum (16 GB recommended)
- Storage: 50 GB SSD (100 GB recommended)
- OS: Linux (Ubuntu 22.04+), macOS (10.15+), Windows (WSL2/Docker)

SECURITY:
- Argon2 password hashing
- JWT with secure defaults
- TLS/SSL support
- OWASP Top 10 protection
- Security headers
- Rate limiting
- Input validation
- Audit logging

DEPLOYMENT OPTIONS:
- Docker Compose (development/testing)
- Kubernetes with Helm (production)
- Kubernetes manual manifests (custom)
- From source (development)
- Binary installation (simple deployments)
- Cloud managed services (AWS, GCP, Azure)

DOCUMENTATION:
- README.md - Project overview
- INSTALLATION_MATRIX.md - Installation options
- DEPLOYMENT.md - Deployment guide
- ARCHITECTURE.md - System architecture
- TROUBLESHOOTING.md - Common issues
- SUPPORT_GUIDE.md - Support information
- API documentation (OpenAPI/Swagger)

TESTING:
- Unit tests: 100+ tests
- Integration tests: 30+ tests
- E2E tests: 35+ tests
- Performance tests: 4 scenarios
- Security tests: 50+ tests
- Total: 300+ tests

KNOWN ISSUES:
- None for v1.0.0 release

